d.  The team provides occupational therapy, physiotherapy and speech and language therapy.  The team also offers a specialist assessment, advisory and therapy service to meet the individuals needs of people with physical disabilities and their carers.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'HelpYourselfSheffield-UK:21795',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(4720,13,0,'PHYSICAL DISABILITY THERAPY TEAM, DISABILITIES DIRECTORATE','Works with adults who have long term physical and communication difficulties in the South of the city.  Provides therapy services, information, advice and onward referral for clients, and works with other agencies to maximize the clients independence.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'HelpYourselfSheffield-UK:21796',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(4721,13,0,'SHEFFIELD COMMUNICATION AIDS SERVICE','Part of the Speech and Language Therapy Agency, South West Sheffield Primary Care Trust.  For people with communication disabilities who would benefit from an aid, especially those with speech or language disability.  An assessment of people\'s needs is led by a Speech and Language Therapist who will help individuals and their carers decide what is the best aid for them.  Individuals are assessed either at Centenary House or in their own home.  Limited loan pool for assessment or short-term trial of equipment.  Referral via speech and language therapy.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'HelpYourselfSheffield-UK:21797',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(4722,13,0,'SOUTH DAY SERVICE','Offers a day service for people with a physical disability.  Staff visit people in their own homes to discuss individual needs, in the form of an assessment and individual programme planning - there is no fixed timetable.  Individual work, group work and recreational activities are offered in a positive social environment and, where appropriate, this work is continued within the home and community.  Referrals to